#Explanation


- Print Sum using Recursion


Explanation:

In the recursive sum, initially, Here we printing sum of numbers in decreasing order by calling recursive  function

Test Cases:

1.  n = 10;
2. If user enter negative number

Example

Input: n = 5

Output: 15


#Explanation END

package vaibhav;

public class Recursie_Sum {
	
	public static int Sum(int n) {
		if(n == 1) {
			return 1;
		}
		
		int Snm1 = Sum(n-1);
		int Sn = n + Sum(n-1);
		return Sn;
	}

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		int n = 5;
		System.out.println(Sum(n));
	}

}
